This paper discusses machine learning techniques for computing value functions derived from Markov decision processes, which are commonly used in reinforcement learning. The paper specifically focuses on Temporal Difference (TD) learning algorithms, which are a sub-class of reinforcement learning methods. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses consistency of the algorithms, which suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MA (Multiagent Systems).
